We take seven different datasets—email-Enron (eE), contact-high-school (chs), contact-primary-school (cps), tags-math-sx (tms), MAG-Geo (MG), coauth-DBLP (cD), NDC-substances (Ns)—from Benson et al. [3] and perform various HLP experiments on them. Also, we use the same k-core based sampling technique as used by Liben-Nowell et al. [11] to reduce the size of MAG-Geo and coauth-DBLP datasets since they are huge hypergraphs. More specifically, we retain only those nodes which have hyperdegree (number of incident hyperedges) greater than a threshold \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
